      "span_text": "It suffices to do so in the stable triangulated category of Voevodsky's motives DM(k, Q) in which DM eff (k, Q) embeds fully faithfully by Voevodsky's cancellation theorem. (Recall that DM(k, Q) is defined as the homotopy category of T = Q tr (A 1 /A 1 − 0)-spectra for the stable motivic model structure; for more details, see  Définition 2.5.27] in the special case where the valuation on k is trivial.) In DM(k, Q), we have an isomorphism",
